Description:
Classic Victorian, so well-positioned, so much potential!
How appealing is this? Behind its classic polychromatic brick and lacework façade, this solid period residence offers comfortable living with wonderful scope to enhance and extend (STCA). Close to Johnston Street's newest cafes, Smith Street boutiques and CBD transport, it offers an updated kitchen opening through French doors to a paved courtyard and potential off-street parking; a spacious living/dining room, two double bedrooms, stylish bathroom and large laundry/utility room. This value-packed home features polished timber floors, new gas heating and HWS.

Description:
Golden entry to inner city living
A modern revelation, this superb two bedroom Victorian terrace boasts the crisp interiors, outdoor entertaining and location that will prove irresistible. Beyond a picture book façade lies a bright, comfortable and modernised home where a lofty entrance hall introduces bedrooms with BIR's and gives way to open plan living. Flooded in light, featuring a stylish CaesarStone kitchen and flowing seamlessly to a paved courtyard garden it presents an easy care indoor-outdoor lifestyle offering easy entertaining. Comfort continues through a chic bathroom, Euro laundry and heating/cooling, while an outstanding location puts everything the inner city is famous for at your door, from Brunswick and Smith Street cafes to Queens Parade shopping, trams, trains and parks, all a mere 3km to the CBD.

Description:
Terrace living in Collingwood
Boasting a stunning heritage facade and in a quintessential Collingwood streetscape, the apartment is complimented by an extra large terrace with abundant natural light throughout. Other features include:
A spacious and light-filled double bedroom with mirrored robes
Designer’s bathroom with matt black signature tapware and a well-appointed Euro laundry
Gourmet kitchen with stone benchtops, quality stainless steel appliances and masses of storage
Large sun-washed living zone extending out to an entertainer’s terrace
Split system heating and cooling, double glazed windows, timber floorboards, intercom entry and a substantial storage cage
This is inner-city living at its best! Desirably located in the heart of Collingwood with everything at your doorstep. Designed by Elenberg Fraser and brought to life by Gurner, 107 Cambridge is one of the last remaining buildings to be completed within the historic ‘Foy and Gibson’ precinct.
Brilliantly positioned, moments from Smith & Gertrude Street’s eclectic mix of boutiques, bars and restaurants and an abundance of public transport options.
Insights: 301/107 Cambridge Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2019 and 49 other 1 bedroom unit in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
"Inner City Gem"
Near new, this development by prominent Melbourne property developer Urban Inc and designed by award winning architects Elenberg Fraser located in the heart of Collingwood's Foy and Gibson heritage precinct.
Boasting plenty of natural light and amazing views , this spacious 2 bedroom apartment features 2 double bedrooms (BIR's), impressive floor to ceiling windows, open-plan living overlooking entertainment balcony, marvellous stone kitchen, modern bathroom, European laundry, split system, NBN, secure lift access, BBQ area, storage cage and basement car space.
Beyond the apartment, the lush exterior landscapes provide occupants with a secure sanctuary to call home. With plenty of options for entertaining whether it be by the rooftop garden terrace or ,a solar heated plunge pool which overlooks Collingwood's decommissioned industrial factories.
Less than 4km from the CBD and even closer proximity to Smith Street bars/cafes/restaurants, Oxley is conveniently located to provide an ideal balance of work and play.
This is an opportunity you can't miss!

Description:
The Idyllic Low-Maintenance, Inner-City Lifestyle
Enjoying a quiet position at the centre of the complex, this immaculately presented apartment presents an exceptional opportunity for first homebuyers and astute investors alike to secure an exemplar of the inner-city lifestyle. The light-filled interior comprises a well-appointed galley kitchen (stainless steel appliances, gas cooking, dishwasher, tile splashback and ample storage) that services the expansive open plan dining and living room with polished timber floors that opens onto a generously proportioned north courtyard, 2 double bedrooms with BIRs and (main with ensuite), central bathroom with Euro laundry, heating, air-conditioning, secure intercom entry and OSP and storage cage on title via Langridge Street. Spoilt with convenience and public transport options, the home is centrally located to all the side-street cafes, bars and boutiques that Collingwood is known for, vibrant Victoria Street restaurants and a short stroll through Fitzroy Gardens to the CBD and the MCG.

Description:
A hidden gem in a lively inner-city locale
Delivering tranquil retreat, this cute-as-a-button, two-bedroom Edwardian home is a rarely found gem amid Collingwood's bustling urban surrounds. Melding endearing period style with luxurious modern comfort, the home provides an indoor-outdoor oasis enhanced by a large yard, dual-entry via service road, and secure off-street parking. Instantly accessible to every lifestyle desire, the home is set among an endless array of scrumptious eateries, boutique bars and public transport, while just a short stroll to Melbourne's sporting precinct, Yarra River recreation, and only 2km to the CBD.
With a spread of lustrous Baltic floors lying beneath high 10-foot ceilings, the home enjoys a spacious atmosphere. A formal lounge room introduces the layout for refined entertaining, while an extended open plan domain flows through a wall of bi-fold doors into a private garden for sun-splashed alfresco dining. Ready to cater to any occasion, the open plan domain entertains guests aside a cosy open fireplace, providing a stylish kitchen with wide cooking appliances and dishwasher among its substantial cabinetry.
Enjoying generous dimensions for relaxing sanctuary, each bedroom is fitted with built-in robes, including two-way access from the master bedroom to a sleek twin-basin bathroom with laundry facilities. Complete with a secured, remote double carport via the rear entry the 247m2 (approx.) allotment offers an effervescent inner-city lifestyle in a blue-chip locale, with the potential for future development (subject to council approval).
Insights: 70 Islington Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2019 and 29 other 2 bedroom house in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
Contemporary Elegance, Coveted Locale
Presenting breathtaking views from it's huge terrace, this stylish and remarkable apartment defines the best of inner city living. Positioned in an outstanding Collingwood location, the residence offers a serene getaway with all the amenities at your fingertips and convenient city access. Light filled open plan living accented by timber floors opens onto an expansive wraparound terrace, taking in city views and providing alfresco dining and entertaining space. The sleek contemporary kitchen features stone benchtops and separate stone island and quality appliances including Miele gas cooktop, oven and integrated dishwasher drawer. Two bright bedrooms feature built in robes and terrace access, with one bedroom benefitting from a northerly aspect, and share a functional bathroom with shower. A European laundry, access to lush communal gardens and secure underground carpark and storage cage complete the home. Ideally situated moments from Smith Street trams and amenities, with the city, Fitzroy Gardens and Carlton Gardens close by.

Description:
Pay out your mortgage sooner!
Hot topics: location, position, outlook, design and layout. Did I mention the extra low owner’s corp fees? If saving money is not a great incentive already, then perhaps you’ll be curious to know more about this apartment.
This is inner-city living, unsurpassed! Desirably located in the heart of Collingwood with everything at your door step. This 1 bedroom + 1 extra room apartment is gorgeous.
Located at the very end of the building, you’ll only have one neighbour on your side, while you can look outside the double glazed windows into Collingwood’s birthmark: red bricks, steel beams and blue sky.
This boutique building was designed by Elenberg Fraser and brought to life by Gurner and is one of the last remaining buildings to be completed within the historic ‘Foy and Gibson’ precinct.
Boasting a stunning heritage facade and in a quintessential Collingwood streetscape, the apartment features:
• A spacious and light –filled double bedroom with mirrored robes
• Generous study/multipurpose room
• Designer 2 way bathroom with matt black signature tapware and a well- appointed Euro laundry
• Gourmet kitchen with stone benchtops and built-in dining table, quality stainless steel appliances and masses of storage
• Large sun-washed living zone extending out to a covered entertainers terrace balcony
• Split system heating and cooling, double glazed windows, timber floorboards, intercom entry, secure parking and a substantial storage cage.
• Located above a wine bar and café, facilities also include a residents library/lounge.
Brilliantly positioned, moments from Smith & Gertrude Street's eclectic mix of boutiques, bars and restaurants and an abundance of public transport options.
Internal area
61m²

Description:
Sensational penthouse-style indoor-outdoor entertainer
Spanning 2 light-flooded levels with 2 extensive entertainment decks, this penthouse-style warehouse apartment is a stunning city-edge lifestyle sanctuary with superb views. The Foy & Gibson precinct is inner-Melbourne's premier warehouse district and sitting atop of the action in complete peace and privacy is this expansive modern apartment. Served by a Smeg-equipped stone kitchen and powder room, the separate dining and living areas on polished concrete flooring open through full-height glazing to the original warehouse-walled deck. Upstairs are a beautifully-renovated bathroom and 2 large bedrooms (BIRs) both adjoining the spectacular 2nd deck. Also offers heating/cooling, laundry, secure car space and storage cage near Smith & Gertrude Streets, cafes, galleries, shops and trams.

Description:
Stylish apartment in vibrant urban precinct
Located in the heart of one of Melbournes most vibrant urban precincts, this sophisticated two-bedroom apartment offers the ultimate northside lifestyle. With an abundance of bars, eateries, live music, and boutiques all within walking distance, its the ideal home base for those wishing to be swept up in the areas eclectic charm.
Inside, timber-laden floors, crisp white walls and a stylish kitchen give the main living area an immediate sense of sophistication. Adjoining the space via double doors is a generous balcony spacious enough for entertaining, outdoor dining or urban garden pursuits. Both bedrooms, one of which shares access to the balcony, have built-in wardrobes and are serviced by a contemporary central bathroom.
Additional features include a European laundry, one undercover car park, a storage unit, dishwasher, and split system. With the number 86 tram only minutes away not to mention all the delights of Brunswick and Gertrude Street within walking distance, this is an outstanding opportunity to secure your very own urban sanctuary.

Description:
Landmark residence in the heart of Collingwood
Strictly By Appointment Only. You must register to attend an inspection. The house won't be open for inspection on Auction Day.
A superb opportunity has arisen to secure a landmark double storey residence offering dual street frontage. Once a button factory and Collingwood's first scout hall, it has been transformed into a deluxe industrial-style abode just a short stroll to vibrant Smith Street and Victoria Park station. Currently utilised as a business, the ground floor has a stunning atrium-style foyer with a wall of bespoke bi-fold doors leading to a huge office or living area with built-in cabinetry. At the back is a large showroom, or master bedroom, with an open fireplace and spacious robes, plus a sparkling twin bathroom and kitchenette. Upstairs is an elegant light-filled living and dining area with a slow combustion fireplace and French doors accessing the private entertaining balcony. There is also a smart granite kitchen with stainless steel gas appliances, king-size bedroom with a walk-in robe and balcony, third robed bedroom and sleek spa bathroom. Features include a European laundry, an alarm, split system a/c throughout, polished floorboards and dual frontage via Harmsworth Lane. In addition, this recently restumped property has had structural reinforcement and its foundations strengthened.
Insights: 73 Harmsworth Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2019 and 24 other 3 bedroom house in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
Penthouse Excellence With Private Rooftop Terrace
Blending textured industrial materials such as exposed concrete ceilings with the finest in luxury fixtures and fittings, this exceptional penthouse apartment is an exemplar of contemporary minimalist style and inner city mode-de-vie. The jewel in the apartment's crown is its impressive private rooftop terrace with a spectacular panoramic vista across the urban skyline to the CBD and B/I gas barbeque, while the elegantly understated interior boasts muted neutral tones throughout and comprises a well-appointed galley kitchen (stainless steel bench tops, island bench with breakfast bar, Smeg cookware and integrated dishwasher, integrated refrigerator and ample storage) that services the dining and living zones that enjoy access to the length-of-the-apartment balcony with uninterrupted views of the CBD skyline (fitted with sun-screen roller shades), bedroom with BIRs, balcony access and northerly aspect, gleaming central bathroom and Euro laundry. Architecturally crafted by DKO with interiors by award winning Collingwood locals DesignOffice, the building commands a captivating street presence both distinct and complimentary to Collingwood's historic urban fabric. Closely located to an innumerable amount of popular side-street restaurants, cafes and bars (including award winning Congress Wine & Espresso at its front door), the apartment is positioned next to Cambridge Street Reserve just a short stroll from iconic Smith and Gertrude Street boutiques and trams. Features include ducted heating and cooling, ceiling fans, double glazed windows, secure video intercom entry, lift access and basement level with secure bicycle parking (B/I tyre pump) and secure storage room. Also included is a lease for a car space. Nelson Alexander Pty Ltd
Insights: 801/47 Peel Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2019 and 49 other 1 bedroom unit in Collingwood have recently been sold.
